<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<title>DuoQ</title>
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', 'http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:300' %>
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', 'http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway' %>
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', 'https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/css/bootstrap.min.css' %>
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
	<%= analytics_init if Rails.env.production? %>
	<style type="text/css">
	html{
		height: 100%;
		width: 100%;
		background-image: radial-gradient(#337ab7, #000);
	}

	.container{
		position: absolute;
		top: 15%;
		left: 0;
		width: 100%;
	}

	.maintenance{
		background-color: #000;
		color: #FFF;
		text-shadow: 1px 0 1px #000;
		font-family: "Open sans";
		background: url(https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/ChvtzIed2CwdxpZ2SPH8oCmAWcLFQdl3Av6RZQ0eD1g=h2160-no);
		background-attachment: fixed;
		background-repeat: no-repeat;
		background-position: left top;
		background-size: cover;
		width: 80%;
		padding: 5em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		margin-left: auto;
		margin-right: auto;
	}

	p{
		font-size: 25px;
	}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<center><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/pAk4TeGtvzt3P4t11xdMu1VP7Uo1D8qMlAJ-I1Rp6hA=w180-no"></center>
		<div class="maintenance">
			<h1>DuoQ</h1>
			<p>Hi !</br>
				DuoQ is down for maintenance cause of Riot validation criteria.
			</p>
			<blockquote>
				<p>Unfortunately, we cannot approve any project to use the third party development tools if they connect to chat, even if it's to provide static data. As for verifying a user's League account.</p>
				<blockquote class="blockquote-reverse">
					Riot Games
				</blockquote>
			</blockquote>
			<p>
				But as the phoenix, we will rebirth from our ashes, see you soon !
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>